<section id="usage">
  <h2>Usage</h2>

  <h3>Basic chat conversation</h3>
  {% set _codeChat %}<!-- Chat container: flex column with gap -->
<section class="chat-window">
  <p data-bubble="system">Today, 2:34 PM</p>

  <p data-bubble="incoming">Hey, have you seen this?</p>
  <p data-bubble="outgoing">Yes! Looks great.</p>

  <p data-bubble="assistant">I can help with that.</p>
  <p data-bubble="thought">Hmm, interesting idea...</p>

  <!-- Typing indicator with animated dots -->
  <p data-bubble="typing">
    <span></span>
    <span></span>
    <span></span>
  </p>

  <p data-bubble="error">Failed to send. Check connection.</p>
  <p data-bubble="system">Alice left the conversation</p>
</section>

<style>
  .chat-window {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--size-s);
    max-width: 500px;
    padding: var(--size-l);
  }
</style>{% endset %}
  <code-block language="html" label="Chat conversation">{{ _codeChat | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>Typing indicator</h3>
  <p>The <code>typing</code> bubble expects three empty <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> children for the animated dot indicators. The animation respects <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code>.</p>
</section>

<section id="accessibility">
  <h2>Accessibility</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use semantic elements (<code>&lt;p&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;blockquote&gt;</code>) for bubble content</li>
    <li>The typing indicator uses <code>opacity</code> animation, not content changes, to avoid screen reader noise</li>
    <li>System messages use <code>text-align: center</code> and a pill shape for visual distinction</li>
    <li>Error bubbles use a colored left border rather than color alone to indicate errors</li>
    <li>All <code>data-morph</code> and typing animations are disabled when <code>prefers-reduced-motion: reduce</code> is active</li>
  </ul>
</section>

